The National Executive Council of Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC) has mandated all its organs and state chapters to embark on nationwide strike on Wednesday, 26th September, 2018 if Federal Government to conclude ongoing negotiation on the new national minimum wage.
The Council which is the highest decision making organ of the labour centre passed the resolution at the NEC meeting held in Abuja, also tasked all the state governments to prioritize payment of pensions and gratuity to retired civil servants.
Ayuba Wabba, NLC president disclosed this while reading the communiqué issued at the end of the meeting. Details later…  KEHINDE AKINTOLA, Abuja  